<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="3" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="4.[209,1381,982,1333]" box="[209,309,982,1008]" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">REMARKS</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[209,1381,982,1333]" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">
<taxonomicName authority="Keferstein, 1862" authorityName="Keferstein" authorityYear="1862" box="[209,577,1014,1040]" class="Polychaeta" family="Hesionidae" genus="Psamathe" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="4" pageNumber="3" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="cirrhata">
<emphasis box="[209,394,1014,1040]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">Psamathe cirrhata</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Keferstein" box="[401,577,1014,1040]" firstAuthor="Keferstein" pageId="4" pageNumber="3" pagination="1 - 147" refId="ref21628" refString="KEFERSTEIN W. 1862. - Untersuchungen uber Niedere Seethiere. Zeitschrift fur wissenschaftliche Zoologie 12: 1 - 147, pls 1 - 11. https: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / page / 44977773" type="journal article" year="1862">Keferstein, 1862</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
might need a modification in the specific epithet. As usual for those times, etymology was not explained, but the h letter modifies the meaning (
<bibRefCitation author="Brown" box="[938,1126,1046,1073]" firstAuthor="Brown" page="206" pageId="4" pageNumber="3" refId="ref19276" refString="BROWN R. W. 1954. - Composition of Scientific Words. George King, Baltimore, 882 p. ark: / 13960 / t 9184 f 72 b" type="book" year="1954">Brown 1954: 206</bibRefCitation>
) from having filaments, or provided with cirri, which is typical for most hesionids (
<emphasis box="[814,898,1080,1105]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">L. cirrus</emphasis>
), to being orange-colored (Gr. cirrho, 
<emphasis box="[1295,1365,1079,1105]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">kirrhos</emphasis>
). However, the term was derived from the German noun for cirri, used several times along the original description and must be corrected for indicating cirri (
<bibRefCitation author="ICZN" box="[655,787,1144,1170]" firstAuthor="ICZN" pageId="4" pageNumber="3" refId="ref21270" refString="ICZN (INTERNATIONAL COMMISSION ON ZOOLOGICAL NOMENCLA- TURE). 1999. - International Code of Zoological Nomenclature, Fourth Edition. The International Trust for Zoological Nomenclature, London, 306 p. https: // www. iczn. org / the-code / theinternational-code-of-zoological-nomenclature / the-code-online /" type="book" year="1999">ICZN 1999</bibRefCitation>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[798,837,1144,1170]" country="Djibouti" name="Arta" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">Art</collectingRegion>
. 32.5.1). 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Southern" baseAuthorityYear="1914" box="[936,1190,1144,1170]" class="Polychaeta" family="Hesionidae" genus="Psamathe" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="4" pageNumber="3" phylum="Annelida" rank="subSpecies" species="fusca" subSpecies="hibernica">
<emphasis box="[936,1190,1144,1170]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">Psamathe fusca hibernica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was originally described as 
<emphasis box="[314,397,1176,1202]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">Castalia</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Savigny" box="[403,549,1176,1203]" firstAuthor="Savigny" pageId="4" pageNumber="3" pagination="1 - 128" refId="ref23583" refString="SAVIGNY J. - C. 1822. - Systeme des annelides, principalement de celles des cotes de l'Egypte et de la Syrie, offrant les caracteres tant distinctifs que naturels des ordres, familles et genres, avec la description des especes. Description de l'Egypte, Paris, Histoire Naturelle 1 (3): 1 - 128. https: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / page / 41329897" type="journal article" year="1822">Savigny, 1822</bibRefCitation>
(accepted as 
<taxonomicName authority="de Blainville, 1828" authorityName="de Blainville" authorityYear="1828" box="[685,995,1176,1203]" class="Polychaeta" family="Hesionidae" genus="Nereimyra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="4" pageNumber="3" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[685,791,1177,1202]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">Nereimyra</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="de Blainville" box="[796,995,1176,1203]" firstAuthor="de Blainville" pageId="4" pageNumber="3" pagination="365 - 625" refId="ref19683" refString="DE BLAINVILLE H. M. D. 1828. - Vers. Dictionaire des Sciences Naturelles 57: 365 - 625. https: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / page / 25316888" type="journal article" year="1828">de Blainville, 1828</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
), but in the brief diagnosis, 
<bibRefCitation author="Southern" firstAuthor="Southern" page="49" pageId="4" pageNumber="3" pagination="1 - 160" refId="ref23852" refString="SOUTHERN R. 1914. - Archiannelida and Polychaeta. Biological survey of Clare Island in the county of Mayo, Ireland and of the adjoining district 2 (47): 1 - 160, pls. 1 - 15." type="journal article" year="1914">Southern (1914: 49)</bibRefCitation>
regarded it as very similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Johnston" authorityYear="1836" box="[633,706,1209,1235]" class="Polychaeta" family="Hesionidae" genus="Psamathe" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="4" pageNumber="3" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="fusca">
<emphasis box="[633,706,1209,1235]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">P. fusca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Hartman" box="[721,952,1209,1236]" firstAuthor="Hartman" page="183" pageId="4" pageNumber="3" pagination="1 - 628" refId="ref20979" refString="HARTMAN O. 1959. - Catalogue of the polychaetous annelids of the World. Allan Hancock Foundation Publications, Occasional Papers 23: 1 - 628." type="journal article" year="1959">Hartman (1959: 183)</bibRefCitation>
included it as a subspecies. The Western Atlantic records of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Keferstein" authorityYear="1862" box="[411,502,1242,1267]" class="Polychaeta" family="Hesionidae" genus="Psamathe" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="4" pageNumber="3" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="cirrata">
<emphasis box="[411,502,1242,1267]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">P. cirrata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Uebelacker" box="[542,740,1241,1268]" firstAuthor="Uebelacker" pageId="4" pageNumber="3" pagination="3" refId="ref24230" refString="UEBELACKER J. M. 1984. - Family Hesionidae Sars, 1862, in UEBELACKER J. M. &amp; JOHNSON P. G. (eds), Taxonomic Guide to the Polychaetes of the Norhtern Gulf of Mexico. Barry A. Vittor &amp; Assoc., Mobile, 7 vols, 3: 28.1 - 28.39." type="journal article" year="1984">Uebelacker (1984)</bibRefCitation>
differ from the Eastern Atlantic forms, and might belong to an undescribed species, because they have smaller eyes, positioned on the posterior prostomial half, and by having neurochaetae with blades 6-20× longer than wide.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
