<paragraph blockId="4.[811,1457,567,848]" box="[813,913,567,593]" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">REMARKS</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[811,1457,567,848]" lastBlockId="5.[130,777,215,656]" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="4" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">
<bibRefCitation author="Pleijel" box="[813,1063,598,624]" firstAuthor="Pleijel" page="122 - 124" pageId="4" pageNumber="3" pagination="89 - 163" refId="ref22905" refString="PLEIJEL F. 1998. - Phylogeny and classification of Hesionidae (Polychaeta). Zoologica Scripta 27: 89 - 163. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1463 - 6409.1998. tb 00433. x" type="journal article" year="1998">Pleijel (1998: 122-124)</bibRefCitation>
reinstated 
<taxonomicName authority="Johnston, 1836" authorityName="Johnston" authorityYear="1836" box="[1178,1451,598,624]" class="Polychaeta" family="Hesionidae" genus="Psamathe" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="4" pageNumber="3" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1178,1277,598,624]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">Psamathe</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Johnston" box="[1282,1451,598,624]" firstAuthor="Johnston" pageId="4" pageNumber="3" pagination="14 - 17" refId="ref21460" refString="JOHNSTON G. 1836. - Illustrations in British Zoology. Magazine of Natural History, Journal of Zoology, Botany, Mineralogy, Geology and Meteorology 9: 14 - 17. https: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / page / 2293068" type="journal article" year="1836">Johnston, 1836</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, clarified its taxonomic history, and provided a list of species, including some new combinations (
<bibRefCitation author="Pleijel" firstAuthor="Pleijel" page="162 - 163" pageId="4" pageNumber="3" pagination="89 - 163" refId="ref22905" refString="PLEIJEL F. 1998. - Phylogeny and classification of Hesionidae (Polychaeta). Zoologica Scripta 27: 89 - 163. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1463 - 6409.1998. tb 00433. x" type="journal article" year="1998">Pleijel 1998: 162- 163</bibRefCitation>
). There are currently five species in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Johnston" authorityYear="1836" box="[1241,1341,693,719]" class="Polychaeta" family="Hesionidae" genus="Psamathe" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="4" pageNumber="3" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1241,1341,693,719]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">Psamathe</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: 
<taxonomicName authority="(Wesenberg-Lund, 1962)" baseAuthorityName="Wesenberg-Lund" baseAuthorityYear="1962" class="Polychaeta" family="Hesionidae" genus="Psamathe" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="4" pageNumber="3" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="ancuda">
<emphasis box="[1354,1455,693,719]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">P. ancuda</emphasis>
(Wesenberg-Lund, 1962)
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[1160,1223,725,751]" name="Chile" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">Chile</collectingCountry>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Keferstein, 1862" authorityName="Keferstein" authorityYear="1862" class="Polychaeta" family="Hesionidae" genus="Psamathe" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="4" pageNumber="3" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="cirrata">
<emphasis box="[1235,1330,726,751]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">P. cirrata</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Keferstein" firstAuthor="Keferstein" pageId="4" pageNumber="3" pagination="1 - 147" refId="ref21628" refString="KEFERSTEIN W. 1862. - Untersuchungen uber Niedere Seethiere. Zeitschrift fur wissenschaftliche Zoologie 12: 1 - 147, pls 1 - 11. https: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / page / 44977773" type="journal article" year="1862">Keferstein, 1862</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingRegion box="[938,1060,757,783]" country="France" name="Haute-Normandie" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">Normandy</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1070,1146,758,784]" name="France" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">France</collectingCountry>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Averincev, 1972)" authorityName="Antarctic." baseAuthorityName="Averincev" baseAuthorityYear="1972" box="[1158,1455,757,783]" class="Polychaeta" family="Hesionidae" genus="Psamathe" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="4" pageNumber="3" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="fauveli">
<emphasis box="[1158,1254,757,783]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">P. fauveli</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Averincev" box="[1268,1447,757,783]" firstAuthor="Averincev" pageId="4" pageNumber="3" pagination="88 - 293" refId="ref18589" refString="AVERINCEV V. G. 1972. - [Benthic polychaetes Errantia from the Antarctic and Subantarctic collected by the Soviet Antarctic Expeditions]. Explorations of the Fauna of the Seas 11 (19), Biological Results of the Soviet Antarctic Expeditions 5, 88 - 293." type="journal article" year="1972">Averincev, 1972</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[876,992,789,815]" name="Antarctica" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">Antarctica</collectingCountry>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Johnston, 1836" authorityName="Johnston" authorityYear="1836" box="[1005,1265,789,815]" class="Polychaeta" family="Hesionidae" genus="Psamathe" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="4" pageNumber="3" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="fusca">
<emphasis box="[1005,1084,789,815]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">P. fusca</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Johnston" box="[1092,1265,789,815]" firstAuthor="Johnston" pageId="4" pageNumber="3" pagination="14 - 17" refId="ref21460" refString="JOHNSTON G. 1836. - Illustrations in British Zoology. Magazine of Natural History, Journal of Zoology, Botany, Mineralogy, Geology and Meteorology 9: 14 - 17. https: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / page / 2293068" type="journal article" year="1836">Johnston, 1836</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
from the British coast in the English Channel, and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gulf" baseAuthorityName="Perkins" baseAuthorityYear="1984" box="[1220,1347,821,847]" class="Polychaeta" family="Hesionidae" genus="Psamathe" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="4" pageNumber="3" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="haploseta">
<emphasis box="[1220,1347,821,847]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">P. haploseta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="PERKINS T. H." journalOrPublisher="Proceedings of the Biological Society of Washington" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="4" pageId="4" pageNumber="3" pagination="555 - 582" part="97" publicationUrl="https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/page/34642384" refId="ref22671" refString="PERKINS T. H. 1984. - New species of Phyllodocidae and Hesionidae, principally from Florida. Proceedings of the Biological Society of Washington 97: 555 - 582. https: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / page / 34642384" title="New species of Phyllodocidae and Hesionidae, principally from Florida" type="journal article" year="1984">Perkins, 1984</bibRefCitation>
) from 
<collectingRegion box="[263,345,215,241]" country="United States of America" name="Florida" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">Florida</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[354,503,215,241]" name="United States of America" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">United States</collectingCountry>
. On the other hand, 
<bibRefCitation author="Pleijel" firstAuthor="Pleijel" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" pagination="89 - 163" refId="ref22905" refString="PLEIJEL F. 1998. - Phylogeny and classification of Hesionidae (Polychaeta). Zoologica Scripta 27: 89 - 163. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1463 - 6409.1998. tb 00433. x" type="journal article" year="1998">Pleijel (1998)</bibRefCitation>
also regarded 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Johnston" authorityYear="1836" box="[397,473,247,273]" class="Polychaeta" family="Hesionidae" genus="Psamathe" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="fusca">
<emphasis box="[397,473,247,273]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">P. fusca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Keferstein" authorityYear="1862" box="[529,623,248,273]" class="Polychaeta" family="Hesionidae" genus="Psamathe" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="cirrata">
<emphasis box="[529,623,248,273]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">P. cirrata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as synonyms, and 
<bibRefCitation author="Parapar" box="[179,454,279,306]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Parapar" page="232" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" pagination="210 - 267" refId="ref22643" refString="PARAPAR J., BESTEIRO C. &amp; MOREIRA J. 2004. - Familia Hesionidae Grube, 1850. Fauna Iberica 25: 210 - 267." type="journal article" year="2004">
Parapar 
<emphasis box="[267,318,279,305]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">et al.</emphasis>
(2004: 232)
</bibRefCitation>
followed it. However, despite the proximity of the 
<typeStatus box="[370,418,311,337]" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">type</typeStatus>
localities for these two species, both in the English Channel, there is no 
<typeStatus box="[585,632,343,369]" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">type</typeStatus>
material and topotype specimens for both species should be compared to corroborate this conclusion. There is one apparent difference regarding the length of ventral cirri according to the original descriptions, and some later illustrations (
<bibRefCitation author="McIntosh" box="[593,766,470,496]" firstAuthor="McIntosh" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" pagination="57 - 70" refId="ref22292" refString="MCINTOSH W. C. 1908. - A Monograph of the British Annelids, Volume 2, Part 1. Polychaeta: Nephthydidae to Syllidae. Ray Society, London, 1 - 232, pls. 43 - 50, 57 - 70. https: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / page / 37823953" type="journal article" year="1908">McIntosh 1908</bibRefCitation>
: pl. 69, fig. 16; Hartmann-Schröder 1996: 133, fig. 5b). In 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Johnston" authorityYear="1836" box="[165,242,534,560]" class="Polychaeta" family="Hesionidae" genus="Psamathe" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="fusca">
<emphasis box="[165,242,534,560]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">P. fusca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
it is short, not reaching the tip of neurochaetal lobes, whereas in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Keferstein" authorityYear="1862" box="[330,426,567,592]" class="Polychaeta" family="Hesionidae" genus="Psamathe" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="cirrata">
<emphasis box="[330,426,567,592]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">P. cirrata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
it is longer, reaching the tip of neurochaetal lobes. The key below regards them as different species based on this feature.
</paragraph>
